verbose_text: It is known that MGMT deficiency results in the inability to repair O6-methylguanine in the DNA, caused by genotoxic stress, which, once accumulated, leads to the translocation of the MutSalpha complex (MSH2 and MSH6) into the nucleus, thus increasing GT mismatch binding activity.
evidence: translocation of the MutSalpha complex (MSH2 and MSH6) into the nucleus
